The paper discusses the topic of sparsifying deep neural networks (DNNs) to reduce their size and improve training efficiency. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and specifically, the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also mentions the use of sparsity in computer vision tasks (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the algorithm presented in the paper involves generating diverse topologies for sparse DNNs, which could potentially be applied in the field of control systems (cs.SY).
